# Legitly Phishing Detection - API Keys Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your API keys

# ====================================
# Required API Keys for Full Workflow
# ====================================

# Google Safe Browsing API Key
# Get it from: https://developers.google.com/safe-browsing/v4/get-started
GOOGLE_SAFE_BROWSING_API_KEY=your_google_safe_browsing_api_key_here

# VirusTotal API Key
# Get it from: https://www.virustotal.com/gui/user/your_username/apikey
VIRUSTOTAL_API_KEY=your_virustotal_api_key_here

# Google Custom Search API Key
# Get it from: https://developers.google.com/custom-search/v1/introduction
GOOGLE_SEARCH_API_KEY=your_google_search_api_key_here

# Google Custom Search Engine ID
# Create search engine at: https://programmablesearchengine.google.com/
GOOGLE_SEARCH_ENGINE_ID=your_custom_search_engine_id_here

# ====================================
# Optional: ChatGPT/OpenAI Integration
# ====================================
# If you want to use AI analysis instead of heuristics:
# 1. Get OpenAI API key from: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
# 2. In n8n, replace "Heuristic Phishing Analysis" node with "ChatGPT" node
# 3. Configure OpenAI credentials in n8n settings
# OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key_here

# ====================================
# How to Use These API Keys in n8n
# ====================================
# Method 1: Set them in n8n's environment variables
#   - Stop n8n
#   - Export these variables in your terminal
#   - Restart n8n
#
# Method 2: Use n8n's UI to set environment variables
#   - Go to Settings > Environment Variables in n8n UI
#   - Add each variable manually
#
# Method 3: Load from .env file (recommended)
#   - Create .env file from this template
#   - Start n8n with: n8n start --env-file=.env
